{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":401,"text":"One of the things I want to establish right from the start"},{"time":2717,"text":"is that not all neurosurgeons wear cowboy boots."},{"time":5747,"text":"I just wanted you to know that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7926,"text":"So I am indeed a neurosurgeon,"},{"time":10335,"text":"and I follow a long tradition of neurosurgery,"},{"time":14262,"text":"and what I'm going to tell you about today"},{"time":15855,"text":"is adjusting the dials in the circuits in the brain,"},{"time":18173,"text":"being able to go anywhere in the brain"},{"time":20128,"text":"and turning areas of the brain up or down"},{"time":22547,"text":"to help our patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24759,"text":"So as I said, neurosurgery comes from a long tradition."},{"time":27709,"text":"It's been around for about 7,000 years."},{"time":31261,"text":"In Mesoamerica, there used to be neurosurgery,"},{"time":34986,"text":"and there were these neurosurgeons that used to treat patients."},{"time":38754,"text":"And they were trying to -- they knew that the brain was involved"},{"time":42680,"text":"in neurological and psychiatric disease."},{"time":45032,"text":"They didn't know exactly what they were doing."},{"time":47193,"text":"Not much has changed, by the way. (Laughter)"},{"time":50007,"text":"But they thought that,"},{"time":51880,"text":"if you had a neurologic or psychiatric disease,"},{"time":53883,"text":"it must be because you are possessed"},{"time":56474,"text":"by an evil spirit."},{"time":58826,"text":"So if you are possessed by an evil spirit"},{"time":60795,"text":"causing neurologic or psychiatric problems,"},{"time":63615,"text":"then the way to treat this is, of course,"},{"time":65636,"text":"to make a hole in your skull and let the evil spirit escape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71319,"text":"So this was the thinking back then,"},{"time":72697,"text":"and these individuals made these holes."},{"time":76841,"text":"Sometimes the patients were a little bit reluctant"},{"time":79824,"text":"to go through this because, you can tell that"},{"time":82239,"text":"the holes are made partially and then, I think,"},{"time":84690,"text":"there was some trepanation, and then they left very quickly"},{"time":86705,"text":"and it was only a partial hole,"},{"time":88606,"text":"and we know they survived these procedures."},{"time":90922,"text":"But this was common."},{"time":92130,"text":"There were some sites where one percent"},{"time":93396,"text":"of all the skulls have these holes, and so you can see"},{"time":96121,"text":"that neurologic and psychiatric disease is quite common,"},{"time":99315,"text":"and it was also quite common about 7,000 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103748,"text":"Now, in the course of time,"},{"time":105901,"text":"we've come to realize that"},{"time":108121,"text":"different parts of the brain do different things."},{"time":110379,"text":"So there are areas of the brain that are dedicated"},{"time":111566,"text":"to controlling your movement or your vision"},{"time":114259,"text":"or your memory or your appetite, and so on."},{"time":117208,"text":"And when things work well, then the nervous system"},{"time":119942,"text":"works well, and everything functions."},{"time":121611,"text":"But once in a while, things don't go so well,"},{"time":123858,"text":"and there's trouble in these circuits,"},{"time":126400,"text":"and there are some rogue neurons that are misfiring"},{"time":129104,"text":"and causing trouble, or sometimes they're underactive"},{"time":132283,"text":"and they're not quite working as they should."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134827,"text":"Now, the manifestation of this"},{"time":136964,"text":"depends on where in the brain these neurons are."},{"time":139448,"text":"So when these neurons are in the motor circuit,"},{"time":141870,"text":"you get dysfunction in the movement system,"},{"time":144282,"text":"and you get things like Parkinson's disease."},{"time":146448,"text":"When the malfunction is in a circuit that regulates your mood,"},{"time":149744,"text":"you get things like depression,"},{"time":152028,"text":"and when it is in a circuit that controls your memory and cognitive function,"},{"time":155852,"text":"then you get things like Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":158373,"text":"So what we've been able to do is to pinpoint"},{"time":161096,"text":"where these disturbances are in the brain,"},{"time":163403,"text":"and we've been able to intervene within these circuits"},{"time":166440,"text":"in the brain to either turn them up or turn them down."},{"time":170096,"text":"So this is very much like choosing the correct station"},{"time":172380,"text":"on the radio dial."},{"time":174355,"text":"Once you choose the right station, whether it be jazz or opera,"},{"time":177004,"text":"in our case whether it be movement or mood,"},{"time":179337,"text":"we can put the dial there,"},{"time":181303,"text":"and then we can use a second button to adjust the volume,"},{"time":184074,"text":"to turn it up or turn it down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186083,"text":"So what I'm going to tell you about"},{"time":187311,"text":"is using the circuitry of the brain to implant electrodes"},{"time":191369,"text":"and turning areas of the brain up and down"},{"time":193837,"text":"to see if we can help our patients."},{"time":195541,"text":"And this is accomplished using this kind of device,"},{"time":197874,"text":"and this is called deep brain stimulation."},{"time":200335,"text":"So what we're doing is placing these electrodes throughout the brain."},{"time":203406,"text":"Again, we are making holes in the skull about the size of a dime,"},{"time":207355,"text":"putting an electrode in, and then this electrode"},{"time":209506,"text":"is completely underneath the skin"},{"time":211734,"text":"down to a pacemaker in the chest,"},{"time":213824,"text":"and with a remote control very much like a television remote control,"},{"time":218352,"text":"we can adjust how much electricity we deliver"},{"time":221331,"text":"to these areas of the brain."},{"time":223399,"text":"We can turn it up or down, on or off."},{"time":226290,"text":"Now, about a hundred thousand patients in the world"},{"time":228945,"text":"have received deep brain stimulation,"},{"time":230821,"text":"and I'm going to show you some examples"},{"time":231975,"text":"of using deep brain stimulation to treat disorders of movement,"},{"time":234686,"text":"disorders of mood and disorders of cognition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239200,"text":"So this looks something like this when it's in the brain."},{"time":241939,"text":"You see the electrode going through the skull into the brain"},{"time":244174,"text":"and resting there, and we can place this really anywhere in the brain."},{"time":247357,"text":"I tell my friends that no neuron is safe"},{"time":249817,"text":"from a neurosurgeon, because we can really reach"},{"time":251999,"text":"just about anywhere in the brain quite safely now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254565,"text":"Now the first example I'm going to show you is a patient"},{"time":257085,"text":"with Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":258795,"text":"and this lady has Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":260782,"text":"and she has these electrodes in her brain,"},{"time":263092,"text":"and I'm going to show you what she's like"},{"time":264374,"text":"when the electrodes are turned off and she has her Parkinson's symptoms,"},{"time":267881,"text":"and then we're going to turn it on."},{"time":270214,"text":"So this looks something like this."},{"time":272909,"text":"The electrodes are turned off now, and you can see that she has tremor."},{"time":277420,"text":"(Video) Man: Okay. Woman: I can't. Man: Can you try to touch my finger?"},{"time":281139,"text":"(Video) Man: That's a little better. Woman: That side is better."},{"time":284764,"text":"We're now going to turn it on."},{"time":288556,"text":"It's on. Just turned it on."},{"time":294561,"text":"And this works like that, instantly."},{"time":297824,"text":"And the difference between shaking in this way and not --"},{"time":300806,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":305407,"text":"The difference between shaking in this way and not is related to the misbehavior"},{"time":309512,"text":"of 25,000 neurons in her subthalamic nucleus."},{"time":313485,"text":"So we now know how to find these troublemakers"},{"time":316061,"text":"and tell them, \"Gentlemen, that's enough."},{"time":317452,"text":"We want you to stop doing that.\""},{"time":318786,"text":"And we do that with electricity."},{"time":320008,"text":"So we use electricity to dictate how they fire,"},{"time":323422,"text":"and we try to block their misbehavior using electricity."},{"time":326884,"text":"So in this case, we are suppressing the activity of abnormal neurons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330328,"text":"We started using this technique in other problems,"},{"time":332890,"text":"and I'm going to tell you about a fascinating problem"},{"time":334292,"text":"that we encountered, a case of dystonia."},{"time":337460,"text":"So dystonia is a disorder affecting children."},{"time":339965,"text":"It's a genetic disorder, and it involves a twisting motion,"},{"time":343027,"text":"and these children get progressively more and more twisting"},{"time":345851,"text":"until they can't breathe, until they get sores,"},{"time":347842,"text":"urinary infections, and then they die."},{"time":349873,"text":"So back in 1997, I was asked to see this young boy,"},{"time":353246,"text":"perfectly normal. He has this genetic form of dystonia."},{"time":356202,"text":"There are eight children in the family."},{"time":358421,"text":"Five of them have dystonia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361780,"text":"So here he is."},{"time":363965,"text":"This boy is nine years old, perfectly normal until the age six,"},{"time":368151,"text":"and then he started twisting his body, first the right foot,"},{"time":372546,"text":"then the left foot, then the right arm, then the left arm,"},{"time":375966,"text":"then the trunk, and then by the time he arrived,"},{"time":379213,"text":"within the course of one or two years of the disease onset,"},{"time":382153,"text":"he could no longer walk, he could no longer stand."},{"time":384473,"text":"He was crippled, and indeed the natural progression"},{"time":387171,"text":"as this gets worse is for them to become progressively twisted,"},{"time":390726,"text":"progressively disabled, and many of these children do not survive."},{"time":396416,"text":"So he is one of five kids."},{"time":398444,"text":"The only way he could get around was crawling on his belly like this."},{"time":402538,"text":"He did not respond to any drugs."},{"time":404494,"text":"We did not know what to do with this boy."},{"time":406434,"text":"We did not know what operation to do,"},{"time":408550,"text":"where to go in the brain,"},{"time":410744,"text":"but on the basis of our results in Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":413517,"text":"we reasoned, why don't we try to suppress"},{"time":415522,"text":"the same area in the brain that we suppressed"},{"time":418619,"text":"in Parkinson's disease, and let's see what happens?"},{"time":422274,"text":"So here he was. We operated on him"},{"time":424061,"text":"hoping that he would get better. We did not know."},{"time":427935,"text":"So here he is now, back in Israel where he lives,"},{"time":432062,"text":"three months after the procedure, and here he is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436115,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":444669,"text":"On the basis of this result, this is now a procedure"},{"time":447290,"text":"that's done throughout the world,"},{"time":448538,"text":"and there have been hundreds of children"},{"time":449833,"text":"that have been helped with this kind of surgery."},{"time":454040,"text":"This boy is now in university"},{"time":456157,"text":"and leads quite a normal life."},{"time":458193,"text":"This has been one of the most satisfying cases"},{"time":460561,"text":"that I have ever done in my entire career,"},{"time":462540,"text":"to restore movement and walking to this kind of child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465917,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472172,"text":"We realized that perhaps we could use this technology"},{"time":475041,"text":"not only in circuits that control your movement"},{"time":477213,"text":"but also circuits that control other things,"},{"time":479165,"text":"and the next thing that we took on"},{"time":480312,"text":"was circuits that control your mood."},{"time":483305,"text":"And we decided to take on depression,"},{"time":485381,"text":"and the reason we took on depression is because it's so prevalent,"},{"time":487640,"text":"and as you know, there are many treatments for depression,"},{"time":490184,"text":"with medication and psychotherapy,"},{"time":492221,"text":"even electroconvulsive therapy,"},{"time":494283,"text":"but there are millions of people,"},{"time":495617,"text":"and there are still 10 or 20 percent of patients with depression"},{"time":498409,"text":"that do not respond, and it is these patients that we want to help."},{"time":501661,"text":"And let's see if we can use this technique"},{"time":503764,"text":"to help these patients with depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506003,"text":"So the first thing we did was, we compared,"},{"time":507853,"text":"what's different in the brain of someone with depression"},{"time":509677,"text":"and someone who is normal,"},{"time":511345,"text":"and what we did was PET scans to look at the blood flow of the brain,"},{"time":514805,"text":"and what we noticed is that in patients with depression"},{"time":517174,"text":"compared to normals,"},{"time":519219,"text":"areas of the brain are shut down,"},{"time":520717,"text":"and those are the areas in blue."},{"time":521982,"text":"So here you really have the blues,"},{"time":523602,"text":"and the areas in blue are areas that are involved"},{"time":527175,"text":"in motivation, in drive and decision-making,"},{"time":529831,"text":"and indeed, if you're severely depressed as these patients were,"},{"time":532326,"text":"those are impaired. You lack motivation and drive."},{"time":535018,"text":"The other thing we discovered"},{"time":536897,"text":"was an area that was overactive, area 25,"},{"time":539386,"text":"seen there in red,"},{"time":540974,"text":"and area 25 is the sadness center of the brain."},{"time":543631,"text":"If I make any of you sad, for example, I make you remember"},{"time":546504,"text":"the last time you saw your parent before they died"},{"time":548791,"text":"or a friend before they died,"},{"time":550424,"text":"this area of the brain lights up."},{"time":551630,"text":"It is the sadness center of the brain."},{"time":553353,"text":"And so patients with depression have hyperactivity."},{"time":556565,"text":"The area of the brain for sadness is on red hot."},{"time":558743,"text":"The thermostat is set at 100 degrees,"},{"time":561400,"text":"and the other areas of the brain, involved in drive and motivation, are shut down."},{"time":564528,"text":"So we wondered, can we place electrodes in this area of sadness"},{"time":567525,"text":"and see if we can turn down the thermostat,"},{"time":569954,"text":"can we turn down the activity,"},{"time":571667,"text":"and what will be the consequence of that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":573789,"text":"So we went ahead and implanted electrodes in patients with depression."},{"time":576916,"text":"This is work done with my colleague Helen Mayberg from Emory."},{"time":579403,"text":"And we placed electrodes in area 25,"},{"time":581337,"text":"and in the top scan you see before the operation,"},{"time":583622,"text":"area 25, the sadness area is red hot,"},{"time":585908,"text":"and the frontal lobes are shut down in blue,"},{"time":588302,"text":"and then, after three months of continuous stimulation,"},{"time":590710,"text":"24 hours a day, or six months of continuous stimulation,"},{"time":593725,"text":"we have a complete reversal of this."},{"time":595499,"text":"We're able to drive down area 25,"},{"time":598338,"text":"down to a more normal level,"},{"time":600290,"text":"and we're able to turn back online"},{"time":602326,"text":"the frontal lobes of the brain,"},{"time":603634,"text":"and indeed we're seeing very striking results"},{"time":605503,"text":"in these patients with severe depression."},{"time":608250,"text":"So now we are in clinical trials, and are in Phase III clinical trials,"},{"time":611152,"text":"and this may become a new procedure,"},{"time":613695,"text":"if it's safe and we find that it's effective,"},{"time":615878,"text":"to treat patients with severe depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619567,"text":"I've shown you that we can use deep brain stimulation"},{"time":622527,"text":"to treat the motor system"},{"time":624614,"text":"in cases of Parkinson's disease and dystonia."},{"time":627060,"text":"I've shown you that we can use it to treat a mood circuit"},{"time":629445,"text":"in cases of depression."},{"time":631095,"text":"Can we use deep brain stimulation to make you smarter?"},{"time":635640,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":637736,"text":"Anybody interested in that?"},{"time":640302,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":642602,"text":"Of course we can, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645590,"text":"So what we've decided to do is"},{"time":647804,"text":"we're going to try to turbocharge"},{"time":650225,"text":"the memory circuits in the brain."},{"time":652430,"text":"We're going to place electrodes within the circuits"},{"time":655166,"text":"that regulate your memory and cognitive function"},{"time":657842,"text":"to see if we can turn up their activity."},{"time":661112,"text":"Now we're not going to do this in normal people."},{"time":663050,"text":"We're going to do this in people that have cognitive deficits,"},{"time":666702,"text":"and we've chosen to treat patients with Alzheimer's disease"},{"time":670161,"text":"who have cognitive and memory deficits."},{"time":672268,"text":"As you know, this is the main symptom"},{"time":674207,"text":"of early onset Alzheimer's disease."},{"time":676630,"text":"So we've placed electrodes within this circuit"},{"time":678824,"text":"in an area of the brain called the fornix,"},{"time":680819,"text":"which is the highway in and out of this memory circuit,"},{"time":683597,"text":"with the idea to see if we can turn on this memory circuit,"},{"time":687025,"text":"and whether that can, in turn, help these patients"},{"time":690274,"text":"with Alzheimer's disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692583,"text":"Now it turns out that in Alzheimer's disease,"},{"time":694901,"text":"there's a huge deficit in glucose utilization in the brain."},{"time":698973,"text":"The brain is a bit of a hog when it comes to using glucose."},{"time":702391,"text":"It uses 20 percent of all your --"},{"time":704151,"text":"even though it only weighs two percent --"},{"time":705666,"text":"it uses 10 times more glucose than it should based on its weight."},{"time":708811,"text":"Twenty percent of all the glucose in your body is used by the brain,"},{"time":711394,"text":"and as you go from being normal"},{"time":713824,"text":"to having mild cognitive impairment,"},{"time":716017,"text":"which is a precursor for Alzheimer's, all the way to Alzheimer's disease,"},{"time":718472,"text":"then there are areas of the brain that stop using glucose."},{"time":721161,"text":"They shut down. They turn off."},{"time":723456,"text":"And indeed, what we see is that these areas in red"},{"time":725738,"text":"around the outside ribbon of the brain"},{"time":727505,"text":"are progressively getting more and more blue"},{"time":729781,"text":"until they shut down completely."},{"time":732953,"text":"This is analogous to having a power failure"},{"time":735312,"text":"in an area of the brain, a regional power failure."},{"time":737855,"text":"So the lights are out in parts of the brain"},{"time":740252,"text":"in patients with Alzheimer's disease,"},{"time":742850,"text":"and the question is, are the lights out forever,"},{"time":745259,"text":"or can we turn the lights back on?"},{"time":748120,"text":"Can we get those areas of the brain to use glucose once again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":751356,"text":"So this is what we did. We implanted electrodes in the fornix"},{"time":753906,"text":"of patients with Alzheimer's disease, we turned it on,"},{"time":756519,"text":"and we looked at what happens to glucose use in the brain."},{"time":760030,"text":"And indeed, at the top, you'll see before the surgery,"},{"time":763292,"text":"the areas in blue are the areas that use less glucose than normal,"},{"time":766656,"text":"predominantly the parietal and temporal lobes."},{"time":768864,"text":"These areas of the brain are shut down."},{"time":770574,"text":"The lights are out in these areas of the brain."},{"time":773249,"text":"We then put in the DBS electrodes and we wait for a month"},{"time":776203,"text":"or a year, and the areas in red"},{"time":777594,"text":"represent the areas where we increase glucose utilization."},{"time":780901,"text":"And indeed, we are able to get these areas of the brain"},{"time":783021,"text":"that were not using glucose to use glucose once again."},{"time":786535,"text":"So the message here is that, in Alzheimer's disease,"},{"time":788887,"text":"the lights are out, but there is someone home,"},{"time":791216,"text":"and we're able to turn the power back on"},{"time":793365,"text":"to these areas of the brain, and as we do so,"},{"time":795671,"text":"we expect that their functions will return."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798607,"text":"So this is now in clinical trials."},{"time":800734,"text":"We are going to operate on 50 patients"},{"time":802635,"text":"with early Alzheimer's disease"},{"time":804613,"text":"to see whether this is safe and effective,"},{"time":806670,"text":"whether we can improve their neurologic function."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809649,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":817129,"text":"So the message I want to leave you with today is that,"},{"time":820077,"text":"indeed, there are several circuits in the brain"},{"time":822681,"text":"that are malfunctioning across various disease states,"},{"time":826607,"text":"whether we're talking about Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":828815,"text":"depression, schizophrenia, Alzheimer's."},{"time":831897,"text":"We are now learning to understand what are the circuits,"},{"time":834927,"text":"what are the areas of the brain that are responsible for"},{"time":837129,"text":"the clinical signs and the symptoms of those diseases."},{"time":839649,"text":"We can now reach those circuits."},{"time":841955,"text":"We can introduce electrodes within those circuits."},{"time":844587,"text":"We can graduate the activity of those circuits."},{"time":847569,"text":"We can turn them down if they are overactive,"},{"time":850821,"text":"if they're causing trouble, trouble that is felt throughout the brain,"},{"time":853778,"text":"or we can turn them up if they are underperforming,"},{"time":856359,"text":"and in so doing, we think that we may be able to help"},{"time":858752,"text":"the overall function of the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861092,"text":"The implications of this, of course, is that we may be able"},{"time":863646,"text":"to modify the symptoms of the disease,"},{"time":865956,"text":"but I haven't told you but there's also some evidence"},{"time":867865,"text":"that we might be able to help the repair of damaged areas of the brain using electricity,"},{"time":872028,"text":"and this is something for the future, to see if, indeed,"},{"time":874480,"text":"we not only change the activity but also"},{"time":876719,"text":"some of the reparative functions of the brain"},{"time":878733,"text":"can be harvested."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880288,"text":"So I envision that we're going to see a great expansion"},{"time":883335,"text":"of indications of this technique."},{"time":885787,"text":"We're going to see electrodes being placed for many disorders of the brain."},{"time":888566,"text":"One of the most exciting things about this is that, indeed,"},{"time":891525,"text":"it involves multidisciplinary work."},{"time":893372,"text":"It involves the work of engineers, of imaging scientists,"},{"time":896174,"text":"of basic scientists, of neurologists,"},{"time":898376,"text":"psychiatrists, neurosurgeons, and certainly at the interface"},{"time":901128,"text":"of these multiple disciplines that there's the excitement."},{"time":904069,"text":"And I think that we will see that"},{"time":906826,"text":"we will be able to chase more of these evil spirits"},{"time":910262,"text":"out from the brain as time goes on,"},{"time":912158,"text":"and the consequence of that, of course, will be"},{"time":914060,"text":"that we will be able to help many more patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916332,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}